  "prompt": "I'm in love with my FWB, should I stop having sex with him cause every time we have sex I get more attached to him?",
  "response": "If you're developing deeper feelings for your FWB (friends with benefits) and the relationship is not reciprocated, it\u2019s important to prioritize your emotional well-being. Continuing to have sex when you\u2019re becoming more attached can lead to heartache if your feelings aren\u2019t mutual. Here\u2019s what you can consider:\n\n1. **Be Honest About Your Feelings**: Reflect on your emotions and decide if it\u2019s worth having an open and honest conversation with him. You could express how you feel and see if he feels the same way. It\u2019s possible he could feel similarly, but you won\u2019t know unless you communicate.\n\n2. **Protect Your Heart**: If you\u2019re certain he doesn\u2019t see the relationship progressing beyond FWB, continuing to have sex might lead to more emotional pain. It\u2019s okay to step back to protect your feelings and allow yourself to heal.\n\n3. **Set Boundaries**: If you decide to continue the FWB arrangement, set clear boundaries for yourself to manage your emotions. However, this can be challenging if you\u2019re already deeply attached.\n\n4. **Take Time for Yourself**: If you choose to stop having sex with him, give yourself space and time to process your feelings. Focus on self-care and activities that bring you joy.\n\n5. **Assess the Relationship**: Consider whether this dynamic is truly fulfilling for you. If you\u2019re looking for a deeper, committed relationship, it might be worth seeking someone who aligns with your goals and values.\n\nUltimately, the decision is yours, but listening to your emotions and prioritizing your mental and emotional health is key. If the situation is causing you distress, stepping back is a valid and healthy choice.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
